# .cursorrules — gestion-productos
# Cursor reads this file to understand the project context and coding style.

## Tech stack
- Backend: Java 17, Spring Boot 3.2, Maven, JPA/Hibernate, MySQL
- Frontend: React 18, Axios
- Tests: JUnit 5, Mockito, AssertJ, MockMvc
- Containers: Docker, Docker Compose

## Java conventions (Backend)
- Always use constructor injection, never @Autowired on fields
- All public methods in the service layer must have complete Javadoc
- Handle exceptions using custom classes in the exception/ package
- Use BigDecimal for monetary values, never double or float
- Apply soft delete (activo=false field), not deleteById()
- Validate input parameters at the beginning of each service method
- Business entity and method names in Spanish (domain language)

## Test conventions
- One test per behavior, not per method
- Test name format: method_context_expectedResult
- Always use @DisplayName with a descriptive label in English
- Mock only external dependencies (repositories, external services)

## React conventions (Frontend)
- Functional components with hooks, no class components
- JSDoc on each component documenting its props
- Always handle three states: loading, error, data
- Show backend validation errors field by field
- Format prices with toLocaleString('en-US', {style:'currency', currency:'USD'})

## What this project contains for practice
- 8 bugs in ProductoService.java (commented as BUG #N)
- 6 bugs in the frontend (productoService.js, App.jsx, components)
- Incomplete Javadoc marked with TODO in several files
- Missing tests marked with TODO in test files
